`,r.jsx(e.p,{children:"End-to-end tests usually run in a browser against a live system (in the case of web, using a test runner that automates the browser). Automated E2E tests can take a long time to run because of the different pieces involved and the scope of the tests. You should try to optimize your testing pipeline to run tests in parallel to finish faster."}),`
`,r.jsx(e.p,{children:"Functional tests alone will not give you enough test coverage to avoid regressions. Unit tests aim to provide code coverage depth, while functional tests provide coverage over the breadth of user test scenarios."}),`
